name: places/ChIJq_CdsK0R2jERbnt545rTebk/reviews/ChZDSUhNMG9nS0VJQ0FnTUNvMnZ6UVNnEAE
text:
{'text': "I recently dined here and had a mixed experience. The food was average overall — the lamb cutlet was decent, but the fries that came with it were unfortunately soggy and lacked the crispness you'd expect.

On a brighter note, the salad bar promotion was definitely worth it. The variety was good, and it offered a refreshing balance to the heavier main dishes. It’s a great deal if you're looking for something lighter or enjoy multiple rounds of fresh greens and sides.

The highlight of the experience was the service. Hairul, in particular, stood out with his excellent service. He was attentive, friendly, and made sure we were well-informed about the ongoing promotions and menu items. His warm hospitality really made a difference and elevated the overall dining experience.

Overall, while the food could use some improvement, the service and the value of the salad bar promo made the visit worthwhile.", 'languageCode': 'en'}

name: places/ChIJq_CdsK0R2jERbnt545rTebk/reviews/ChZDSUhNMG9nS0VMNzV0SXF3NWNyVWJnEAE
text: {'text': 'this review is long overdue given how often i frequent this place. i remember my mother and i being absolutely blown away by the salad bar the first time we went — everything was prepared well, especially their creamed spinach, sweet potato fries and truffle angel hair spaghetti. salad bar access comes with every order of main ($14.90++) which honestly, no complaints, extra protein is good. their truffle aburi and mentaiko is great if you like these flavour profiles. a definite must try if you want to be filled and satisfied without breaking the bank', 'languageCode': 'en'}

name: places/ChIJq_CdsK0R2jERbnt545rTebk/reviews/ChZDSUhNMG9nS0VJQ0FnTURJdVpXWFpnEAE
text:
{'text': 'They first thing this restaurant caught my eyes is the unlimited salad bar. The staff welcome us to take a look that their salad bar. It looks more towards a side dish bar instead, but we are more than happy to try it out.

Everyone that orders a main gets the unlimited salad bar, which is really affordable.

Although the chicken steak and baked rice is rather average tbh. Just choose your favourite flavour and you are good to go for the side dishes.

Side dishes are rather extensive and they are still warm, which is always good. The staffs are quick to refill the salad bar.

Personally i like mash potato the most. You can request some peppers from the staff and it will tastes wonders.

Sweet potato fries is a good add on as well.

Overall, a great and satisfying experience.', 'languageCode': 'en'}

name: places/ChIJq_CdsK0R2jERbnt545rTebk/reviews/ChZDSUhNMG9nS0VJQ0FnSURfdjRqZU1BEAE
text: {'text': 'The concept of an unlimited salad bar is really appealing but too bad I am kinda on a diet so couldn’t eat much. Theres even spaghetti and sweet potato fries. Every order of a main dish comes with the unlimited salad bar, got the grilled fish for around $14+ and it was well worth in my opinion. If you’re really hungry and craving for protein, I feel like this place can be a really good spot. Service could be better though, just average.', 'languageCode': 'en'}

text: {'text': 'Food portions are ok meaning not too much or too little. The fries can be cooked better. Love the salad bar. Maybe if i come again, I will just have the salad bar. Service staff are very good here and attentive.\nGood job crew in ensuring the diners have a good experience.\nSalad bar for me is the win here too. Items are replenished promptly and all taste nice.', 'languageCode': 'en'}
